    {
      "sentence_id": 761,
      "text": "17 \n\n\n\n139 \n\nIn 1803, the company's charter was renewed for \na term, to end on the first of July, 1825, but as they \nhave never prosecuted this trade with any degree \nof spirit, arid various subsequent events have mate* \nrially altered the arrangements of the commercial \nworld, ships from the United States and Europe are \npermitted to import articles, the growth and manu- \nfacture of their respective countries, and of Asia; \nexcepting spirits distilled from the sugar cane, \nopium, tobacco, and gun-powder, the sale of which \narticles is strictly forbidden in the Philippines ; the \ntwo latter especially, under severe penalties, being \nroyal monopolies.",
